### Phase 3: Backend Services

#### [NEW] [ocr_service.py](file:///e:/EgnaStudier/1.%20Egna%20studier%20-%20välsorterad/Antigravity_IDE/EduGuide/services/ocr_service.py)
- Accept uploaded image, send to Google Vision API
- Return extracted text + detected language
- Fallback: if Vision API unavailable, return placeholder text for testing

#### [NEW] [ai_service.py](file:///e:/EgnaStudier/1.%20Egna%20studier%20-%20välsorterad/Antigravity_IDE/EduGuide/services/ai_service.py)
- **Subject detection**: Identify if question is Math, Science, Language, etc.
- **Reformulate**: Generate 3 versions of the question (Simple, Context-based, Step-by-step)
- **Hint generation**: Progressive hints based on persona style
- **Answer validation**: Compare student answer against expected answer without revealing it
- All prompts persona-aware (Explorer uses space analogies, Gamer uses game terms, etc.)

#### [NEW] [xp_service.py](file:///e:/EgnaStudier/1.%20Egna%20studier%20-%20välsorterad/Antigravity_IDE/EduGuide/services/xp_service.py)
- Calculate XP: +10 first try, +5 with hints
- Track streaks, total XP
- Growth mindset messages (never negative)

---

### Phase 4: Parent Dashboard

#### [NEW] [parent.html](file:///e:/EgnaStudier/1.%20Egna%20studier%20-%20välsorterad/Antigravity_IDE/EduGuide/templates/parent.html)
- PIN entry screen for access
- Stats overview: total sessions, XP earned, time spent
- Bar chart: subjects studied (using Chart.js via CDN)
- "Struggle areas" list: concepts where student needed most hints
- Session history timeline

